  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TNT2">
<l>pāruruvi nīrerikāl vicumpu mākip</l>
<l>palvēṟu camayamumāyp parantu niṉṟa</l>
<l>ēruruvil mūvarumē yeṉṉa niṉṟa</l>
<l>vimaiyavartan tiruvuruvē ṟeṇṇum pōtu</l>
<l>ōruruvam poṉṉuruva moṉṟu centī</l>
<l>yoṉṟumā kaṭaluruva mottu niṉṟa</l>
<l>mūvuruvuṅ kaṇṭapō toṉṟāñ cōti</l>
<l>mukiluruva memmaṭika ḷuruvan tāṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>When considering the sacred forms of the celestials  [as] different</l>
<l rend="indent">who remain called the Three in beautiful forms</l>
<l>Which remain pervasive as the many various creeds,</l>
<l rend="indent">[and] being the wide earth, water, fire, wind, and the sky,</l>
<l>When seeing [these] three forms which endure</l>
<l rend="indent">one form is golden, one form is red fire, and one like the form of the dark sea -</l>
<l>The light that is One is the form of our god of the cloud-[like] form.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
